        "title": "Snowflake-Style IDOR Attack - Fintech PyME Argentina",
        "subtitle": "Broken Access Control in Loan API",
        "description": "Fiction Notice: Educational scenario. 'CreditoRápido S.A.' is fictitious. Real regulations are cited (Ley 25.326, AAIP).\n\nAn Argentine fintech with 45,000 customers faces an IDOR enumeration attack on its loan API. An attacker with a stolen JWT from a former employee is extracting massive data. As AppSec Lead, you must identify the vulnerable endpoint and patch it. As CISO, you must decide whether to proactively notify the AAIP given the lack of explicit legal obligation in the current law.",
        "difficulty": "expert",
        "estimated_duration_minutes": 50,
